## CODING STANDARDS

This section outlines the coding standards to be followed in the project.  Code must be well-formatted, readable, and maintainable.  Adherence to PEP 8 is expected.  Ruff is the designated formatter and linter.  See the README for usage instructions.  Python 3.13 should be used as the default version for new projects. Minimum Python version: 3.10 (added 2025-05-01). `pyproject.toml` should be configured to use an `indent-width` of 4 spaces.  Lint errors should be addressed one by one.  Long lines should be broken up to comply with the 120-character limit. Method signatures should be formatted with line breaks for better readability. Unused variables should be removed or renamed (e.g., `field_info` to `_field_info`).  The `pyproject.toml` file should include a `[project.optional-dependencies]` section with a `dev` key to specify development dependencies.  These dependencies should be installed using `uv sync`.  The `pyproject.toml` file should include instructions on how to install development dependencies using `uv sync`. The `pyproject.toml` file should include a `[tool.setuptools]` section specifying modules to include in the package to avoid "Multiple top-level modules discovered" errors.  For example: `[tool.setuptools]\npy-modules = ["server"]`
The `proto-to-mcp` package should include a `py.typed` marker to enable type inference.  The `pyproject.toml` file should include `[tool.setuptools.package-data]\n"proto_to_mcp" = ["py.typed"]` to ensure the `py.typed` file is included in distributions.
Pyright is used for type checking instead of mypy.  Message classes should be generated with type annotations using the pipe operator (`|`) for union types where appropriate.  For repeated fields, use `list[{python_type}] | None`.  For non-repeated fields, use `{python_type} | None`.  To avoid "AdditionalInfoEntry" or similar undefined errors, ensure that all classes (including enums) are defined before they are referenced.  Enum classes should be generated using the structure demonstrated in the updated `generator.py` file.


